headline: Elevance Stock Falls 11% After Earnings. What It Means for UnitedHealth, Other Insurers.
summary: The health insurer now expects 2025 earnings of just $30 a share, citing ongoing and industry-wide impact of elevated cost trends in ACA and Medicaid.

headline: Most Managed Care Insurers Expected To See Q2 2025 Drops In Revenue, Net Income
